class=\"pstrut\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathit mtight\">D</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">\u200b</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\"></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Cost\u00a0of\u00a0debt</span></span></span></span><span class=\"\"><span class=\"pstrut\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"></span><span class=\"mord mathit\">E</span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Market\u00a0value\u00a0of\u00a0the\u00a0firm\u2019s\u00a0equity</span></span></span></span><span class=\"\"><span class=\"pstrut\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"></span><span class=\"mord mathit\">D</span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Market\u00a0value\u00a0of\u00a0the\u00a0firm\u2019s\u00a0debt</span></span></span></span><span class=\"\"><span class=\"pstrut\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"></span><span class=\"mord mathit\">V</span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathit\">E</span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mord mathit\">D</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span><span class=\"\"><span class=\"pstrut\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"></span><span class=\"mord mathit\">E</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathit\">V</span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Percentage\u00a0of\u00a0financing\u00a0that\u00a0is\u00a0equity</span></span></span></span><span class=\"\"><span class=\"pstrut\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"></span><span class=\"mord mathit\">D</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathit\">V</span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Percentage\u00a0of\u00a0financing\u00a0that\u00a0is\u00a0debt</span></span></span></span><span class=\"\"><span class=\"pstrut\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathit\">T</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\"><span class=\"\"><span class=\"pstrut\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathit mtight\">c</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">\u200b</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\"></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Corporate\u00a0tax\u00a0rate</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">\u200b</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\"></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>\ufeff\n", "\nProvided a company is expected to perform well, you can usually obtain debt financing at a lower effective cost. For example, if you run a small business and need $40,000 of financing, you can either take out a $40,000 bank loan at a 10%\u00a0interest rate, or you can sell a 25%\u00a0stake in your business to your neighbor for $40,000.\n", "\nSuppose your business earns a $20,000 profit\u00a0during the next year. If you took the bank loan, your interest expense (cost of debt financing) would be $4,000, leaving you with $16,000 in profit.\n", "\nConversely, had you used equity financing, you would have zero debt (and as a result,\u00a0no interest expense), but would keep only 75%\u00a0of your profit (the other 25%\u00a0being owned by your neighbor). Therefore, your personal profit would only be $15,000, or (75% x $20,000).\n"]}